# Event Calendar Plugin

Event Calendar Plugin is a WordPress plugin that allows you to display a calendar with events in your WordPress site.

## Installation

1. Download the plugin zip file .
2. Upload the plugin zip file to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory of your WordPress installation.
3. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress.

## Usage

1. After activating the plugin, you can create events by going to 'Events' > 'Add New' in the WordPress admin panel.
2. When creating or editing an event, you can set the event date using the 'Event Date' meta box.
3. Once you've added events, you can display the event calendar on any page or post by using the shortcode `[event_calendar]`.

## Features

- Create events with a title, description, and event date.
- Display a calendar with events for the current month.
- Clickable event titles linked to event single pages.

## Frequently Asked Questions

### How do I display the event calendar on my site?

To display the event calendar, simply add the shortcode `[event_calendar]` to any page or post where you want the calendar to appear.

### Can I customize the appearance of the event calendar?

Yes, you can customize the appearance of the event calendar by modifying the CSS styles in your theme's stylesheet or by using custom CSS in the WordPress Customizer.

